{"id": "EUVD-2025-12873", "enisaUuid": "ddbd6c68-55cb-30e6-85c8-ce26dd71a2d7", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet/smc: Fix possible leaked pernet namespace in smc_init()\n\nIn smc_init(), register_pernet_subsys(&smc_net_stat_ops) is called\nwithout any error handling.\nIf it fails, registering of &smc_net_ops won't be reverted.\nAnd if smc_nl_init() fails, &smc_net_stat_ops itself won't be reverted.\n\nThis leaves wild ops in subsystem linkedlist and when another module\ntries to call register_pernet_operations() it triggers page fault:\n\nBUG: unable to handle page fault for address: fffffbfff81b964c\nRIP: 0010:register_pernet_operations+0x1b9/0x5f0\nCall Trace:\n  <TASK>\n  register_pernet_subsys+0x29/0x40\n  ebtables_init+0x58/0x1000 [ebtables]\n  ...", "datePublished": "2025-05-01T15:31:52", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-11T03:30:27", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49905", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/61defd6450a9ef4a1487090449999b0fd83518ef", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/62ff373da2534534c55debe6c724c7fe14adb97f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c97daf836f7caf81d3144b8cd2b2a51f9bc3bd09"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49905", "GHSA-8fmx-5gmc-pfcw"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0a31c3d5-099c-3780-9458-c5cc4713a038", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.14"}, {"id": "1052cb46-5c53-3d3d-a343-2b14240521a7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0.8"}, {"id": "55a16679-638c-3929-9868-d314ad4359a0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "194730a9beb52d2b030ea45e12d94868d4a0e6fd <c97daf836f7caf81d3144b8cd2b2a51f9bc3bd09"}, {"id": "5b65d078-19df-3972-aec0-a4cc59d6d212", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "72f2036f-f772-3868-a2a8-1ea394772dde", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.78"}, {"id": "ae4b2cb9-02fc-38ca-a7dd-92207bb94690", "produ